📘 README Instructions: Setting NEBUIS_API_KEY Across Operating Systems
To use the Nebius API in this project, you’ll need to define your API key as an environment variable named NEBUIS_API_KEY. Here's how to set it up depending on your operating system:

🪟 Windows (Command Prompt or PowerShell)
cmd
set NEBUIS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
✅ This sets the variable for the current session. To make it persistent, add it to your system environment variables via Control Panel → System → Advanced → Environment Variables.

🐧 Linux (Bash or Zsh)
bash
export NEBUIS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
✅ To make it persistent, add the line above to your ~/.bashrc, ~/.zshrc, or relevant shell config file.

🍎 macOS (Terminal)
bash
export NEBUIS_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
✅ For persistence, add it to your ~/.zprofile, ~/.bash_profile, or ~/.zshrc depending on your shell.

Once set, your application will be able to access the key using Python’s os.environ:

python
import os
api_key = os.environ.get("NEBUIS_API_KEY")

